{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-02707/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-02707"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:27:07"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan, tilt"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A shadowy staircase."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-02707","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-02707"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/canvas/1/8a373efe-5224-4b1a-bafb-947e294ba125","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T15:01:57.451Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The work featured in Reynolds’s studio is Welsh artist <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW250113653 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artworks/john-young-woman-holding-a-black-cat-n05744\"><u>Gwen John’s painting </u><em><u>Young Woman Holding a Black Cat </u></em><u>(c. 1918-1922)</u></a>, an oil on canvas in the collection of the Tate in London. Though the version featured in the film is likely areproduction, John painted numerous versions of the portrait, <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW250113653 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/481489\"><u>including a smaller iteration now in the collection of the Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York.</u></a> The sitter was the artist’s neighbor in Meudon, just outside of Paris. Although this model appears in nearly fifty of John’s paintings, including <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW250113653 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artworks/john-the-convalescent-n04861\"><em><u>The Convalescent </u></em><u>(1918-1919)</u></a>, her name is unknown. Formally trained at the Slade School of Art—the only academy in Britain that accepted women—in the 1890s, John herself served as an artist’s model after relocating to Paris in 1904, most famously posing for Auguste Rodin, with whom she pursued a decade-long affair. That John, a queer woman, repeatedly returned to the subject of<em>Young Woman Holding a Black Cat </em>as a sitter suggests entanglements of inspiration, artistic creation, and desire that permeate the relationship between artist and muse.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-02707/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:54.26648721399726,478.6271870794078,502.6110363391656,534.9125168236877"}}}]}]}]}